According to reports, teenagers have mixed disinfectant with alcohol-containing mouthwash to get a stronger drink.
The pleasant smells of disinfectant can attract younger children.
The child doesn’t think this is bad for him,” Lopez said.
Many of the more interesting (hand cides) are those with added fragrance.
There are disinfectants with strawberry, grape and orange scents that are very attractive to children.
Hand disinfectant can contain anything between 45 and 95 percent alcohol.
In young children, in particular, only a few injections are needed for alcohol intoxication.
It’s really concentrated alcohol,” said Dr. Stephen Thornton, director of the University of Kansas Hospital Poison Information Center, to Fox 4 in Kansas City.
So don’t leave the whisky shot lying on the table, but hand disinfectant is left out, and if children are interested in it, it’s a quick way to drink a lot of alcohol.
Nhaijah Russell is a six-year-old girl who recently swallowed only four sprays of strawberry-scented hand disinfectant at school and was taken to first aid for treatment.
His blood alcohol level was .179, which is twice as high as the limit for drunken driving in adults, says Chris Ritchey, a first-aid clinician who took care of the girl at the Gwinnet Medical Center outside Atlanta.
