Doctors followed her overnight in a separate children’s hospital for possible brain injury, as alcohol caused the girl to fall and hit her head,” Ritchey said.
It was really frightening,” Nahijah’s mother Ortoria Scott said to CNN.
The situation could have been deadly for my child.
Lopez has recommended that parents and teachers use non-alcoholic products or disinfectant wipes and remove disinfectant from the reach of children.
In addition to alcohol poisoning, some disinfectants are associated with death.
